I have been riding motorcycles for over 40 years and in the past have owned several Yamaha motorcycles. They were always reliable and a real pleasure to ride. That is why I was so happy when I heard Yamaha was coming out with the 150cc Exciter. It was the bike I had been waiting for. After taking delivery of it, I was pleased with its great motor and beautiful lines. However, I soon realized the front suspension was not right. Any small bump in the road caused a loud clunking sound and a jolt to my arms. I took the bike back to where I purchased it and was told it was a common problem. The mechanics at the shop said they would fix it. For a week or two it was a bit better but not much. And since then it has become as bad as ever. I really feel that the bike is dangerous with its current fork set up. Doing research online, I see that the weak front suspension is a common complaint among Yamaha Exciter owners. As a huge fan of Yamaha, I am really disappointed. Did the people that designed the front suspension actually ride the bike before releasing it on the market? I am writing this message in order to ask Yamaha for advice. Is there any way to improve the bike"s current front suspension? If not, I will sadly have to sell this bike. It will be my last Yamaha purchase.
